4. If $l \subset \alpha$, $m \subset \alpha$, $l \cap m = A$, $l \parallel \beta$, $m \parallel \beta$, then $\alpha \parallel \beta$.

Among these, the false proposition(s) is (are) ( )
A: ①
B: ②
C: ③
D: ④

